Exit Polls
Live conversations with correspondents and voters on a history-making day. Tap play to tune in from 4-8 p.m. Eastern time.
A divided nation is deciding on a leader to represent it.
Will a result come quickly, or will it be days, or weeks, before we have a winner?
We tracked when states finish voting and how to watch for results in the states that matter the most.
Follow our hour-by-hour breakdown to see what we’ll know when.
No matter when, how or how often you want election night coverage, we’ve got you covered.
Here’s a look at the last major pre-election polls released in five swing states, with an eye toward what they say about the way the broader winds are blowing.
Hillary Clinton’s narrow loss refocused the party’s efforts to reclaim support and power after years of Republican statehouse dominance.
If President Trump is able to outrun polls in Pennsylvania, it will be because he re-energized white, blue-collar voters in places like Butler County.
If there’s no result by Tuesday night, which is likely to be the case, how will we hang on until there is?

With Winter Coming and Trump Still in Charge, Virus Experts Fear the WorstRegardless of the election results, President Trump will be the one directing the government’s pandemic response as infections climb.
A rapid coronavirus test falters in people without symptoms, a new study found.
Adapting to the pandemic, one Mexican city put its annual tradition of selecting the best mourner in the country online.
A dual listing in Shanghai and Hong Kong was postponed one day after regulators summoned executives from the Ant Group.
Our book critic Dwight Garner has a new collection of his favorite quotations. Check it out.
Meet the Ebony Anglers, a team of five Black women in competitive fishing.
